---
import ServiceLayout from '../../components/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Skill Building OT"
  description="Occupational therapy skill building in Pakenham. If disability or trauma is impacting your daily functioning, we help build skills to increase independence."
  image="/images/services/skill-building.jpg"
>
  <img src="/images/services/skill-building.jpg" alt="Skill building occupational therapy session" class="hero-image" />

  <h2>What to Expect</h2>
  <p>At ATS, we recognize that skill building encompasses both a top-down and bottom-up approach. This means that we delve into identifying the root causes of presenting issues while also addressing the everyday challenges posed by disability. As such, parent coaching sessions are run in conjunction with Skill Building OT.</p>

  <p>Examples of a bottom-up approach include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/services/primitive-reflex-integration/">Primitive Reflex Integration</a></li>
    <li>Sensory Motor Integration</li>
    <li><a href="/services/art-therapy/">Art Therapy</a></li>
  </ul>

  <p>Examples of a top-down approach include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/services/social-skills-group-therapy/">Social Connection Group</a></li>
    <li>Supported Volunteering</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Here's what to expect when getting started with our skill-building Occupational Therapy service.</p>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Initial Assessment via Telehealth</h3>
        <p>The purpose of this session is to gather as much information about you as possible.</p>
        <p>Let's get to know each other and identify what you need and how we can help.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Face to Face at home or school</h3>
        <p>The purpose of these sessions are to identify what motivates the individual, develop rapport and develop goals.</p>
        <p>For rural & remote clients, this step is achieved via collaboration with school teachers, family and other allied health providers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Outcome Assessment</h3>
        <p>We will conduct an assessment that helps us track progress. It will be conducted again at the end of the therapy block to show the achieved outcomes or identify skills that still need developing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">4</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Individual Program Development</h3>
        <p>A therapy plan will be completed to identify the frequency and type of services required.</p>
        <p>Therapy blocks typically span over 3 months, aiming to achieve a single goal before moving onto the next goal in a following therapy block.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="image-gallery">
    <img src="/images/services/skill-building-outdoor.jpg" alt="Outdoor skill building therapy activity" loading="lazy" />
    <img src="/images/services/top-down-bottom-up.png" alt="Top-down and bottom-up approach to skill building" loading="lazy" />
  </div>
</ServiceLayout>
